s up to lvl 20, all on a blue server. Ive done raids of every kind. Im just BORED now. Raids arent fun, exping is boring, loot is meaningless, so I am thinking of trying out a zek.<br>
<br>
I just read an awsome post about life on the Zek's, it looks like the kind of thing I would like. So I now have a few questions, forgive me if they seem trivial to you pvp vets, but Im new to this hehe.<br>
<br>
Before the sanctuary lvls, I made a character on there to see what it was like. Basically it was die, zone, lose newbie tunic, die on the way back to my corpse, rinse repeat. Some people told me it wasnt like that after a certain lvl (different servers had different lvls that it "got better" at, but all seemed to say basically the same thing). <br>
<br>
So, what is it like at mid to high lvls (20+)? Is it bascially just regular everquest except that you dont have to type /d before you fight? Is pking something that happens regularly? Have any of you made groups for the soul purpose of hunting other players (hehe sounds like it would be fun, not sure if its done tho)? Do players actually set out on certain days with the soul purpose of picking a fight, or is that considered against the "unwritten rules"? Is pking something that will give me a bad rep (bad rep as opposed to a blue server bad rep "hes a ninja looter, dont group with him", just an example) or is it over looked?<br>
<br>
Also, what classes are the best for this type of play? I am an avid duler on my server, but dueling seems to be completely different from pvp. On a blue server, dueling a Bard if you are a melee is considered suicide for example. The reason for that is song kiting, but on a Zek, it would seem that, that method of killing would be to slow to be really deadly. What classes seem to be the best at this? Rogues I know have awsome damage output, but our hit points are low. Or would a caster be more deadly? I would like to play something that is able to defend himself, and finish a fight that I start. Basically I dont want to spend most of my on-line time looking for my corpse rather than having fun.<br>
<br>
Once again, my appologies if these questions are stupid. <br>
<br>
Thanks for any info <p><b>Morek Swifthands<br>
Rake of the 51st season</b><br> Ring Warden of Bertox<br><i>Help keep AC prices low... buy stat gear!</i><br><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukambic.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kambic</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/19/01 11:34:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm15.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=264.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Im bored...</span><hr size=1> Well I've only played on RZ primarily, so can't tell you much about the team servers, other then that they are an entirely different world :)<br>
<br>
On Rallos, yes, past about level 15-20 or so, the random PK'ing drops off quickly, but it's never completely gone. There are plenty of unwritten rules, and I could probably write a book on them, and when they do/don't apply, the variations, etc. you pretty much have to play and just learn them hehe. Never played on a blue server, I can't be more then vague about the differences there either. Generally, random PK'ing is frowned on, but there are guilds who have that as their primary goal. These people are often despised, especially those who use less then honorable tactics to accomplish their goals. There are guilds who oppose these people (like mine).<br>
<br>
On occasion people will form groups to hunt other people, but on RZ it's not really that common. Because of only a +-4 level range, you can't always find people to hunt, and tracking them down is hard as well. Plus there are many ways to escape, especially if your a caster.<br>
<br>
Rogues are very good at PvP, moreso if they are the attacker. With a good backstab, a quad, poison, and a successful disarm you can really knock an opponent off their feet if they aren't paying attention. Lag kills ya though :/<br>
<br>
Anyway I suggest trying it out on Rallos, play to at least 20 before deciding... if you can handle it ;p<br>
<br>
